# Claude Code runtime artifacts (the tracked skills under .claude/skills/ stay).
.claude/scheduled_tasks.lock

# Verbatim Uranium source extracted by recon scripts. Per CLAUDE.md, never commit.
# Summaries (reference/*.md) are derived and OK to track; raw dumps are not.
reference/scripts_dump/
reference/maps_dump/
reference/dat_dump/
# Generated real-art tile-map overlay (S8a); load_tile_map prefers it over the
# committed tileset_map.json. Regenerated each assembly; never committed.
reference/tileset_map.gen.json

# Vendored engine (pokeemerald-expansion in engine/). Its own .gitignore keeps
# build/ + *.gba out. Below are rpg2gba PIPELINE-generated artifacts the assembler
# writes INTO the engine tree — regenerated, never committed. A general convention
# for ALL Uranium maps is a BUILD_PLAN follow-up; the pathfinder slice paths are
# listed explicitly for now. The assembler NO LONGER edits tracked upstream files in
# place: data/event_scripts.s + map_data_rules.mk carry committed, stable include-hooks
# and all per-slice content lands in the generated *.gen.json / *.inc files below.
# See engine/RPG2GBA_VENDOR.md.
engine/data/scripts/CommonEvents.inc
engine/data/scripts/uranium_flags.h
engine/data/scripts/uranium_map_aliases.h
engine/data/scripts/Map*_dispatch.pory
engine/data/maps/uranium_includes.inc
engine/data/maps/map_groups.gen.json
engine/data/layouts/layouts.gen.json
# S8a tileset graphics: generated engine fragments (pulled in by committed sentinel
# #include hooks in src/data/tilesets/*.h + include/tilesets.h) and the emitted art.
engine/src/data/tilesets/uranium_graphics.gen.h
engine/src/data/tilesets/uranium_metatiles.gen.h
engine/src/data/tilesets/uranium_tilesets.gen.h
engine/include/uranium_externs.gen.h
engine/include/uranium_walker_maps.h
engine/data/tilesets/primary/uranium*/
engine/data/tilesets/secondary/uranium*/
# Task-4 NPC sprites: generated engine fragments (pulled in by committed sentinel
# #include hooks in include/constants/event_objects.h, src/data/object_events/*.h,
# and src/event_object_movement.c) and the emitted sprite sheets.
engine/include/constants/uranium_event_objects.gen.h
engine/src/data/object_events/uranium_*.gen.h
engine/graphics/object_events/pics/uranium/
# Full-corpus Map Walker build: the assembler generates a per-map dir under
# data/maps/ and data/layouts/ for every built Uranium map (~190) plus the
# UraniumWalkerStub/ dummy for dropped stock map data. Blanket-ignore all per-map
# dirs — the pristine STOCK dirs are already tracked, so git keeps them; this only
# keeps the generated (Uranium + stub) dirs out of `git status` so ROM-derived
# binaries are never accidentally committed (CLAUDE.md §2).
engine/data/maps/*/
engine/data/layouts/*/
